      • integrate_rational_function_list

        public static Expr[][] integrate_rational_function_list(Expr p,
                                                        Expr q,
                                                        Expr x)
        Integration of a rational function in Q(x)
        Parameters:
        p - - a polynomial in Q[x]
        q - - a polynomial in Q[x]
        x - - a variable
        Returns:
        the list [[v_0], [c_1, v_1], ..., [c_k, v_k]] such that
        p/q = diff(v_0, x) + sum(c_i*diff(v_i, x)/v_i, i, 1, k)

      • integrate_rational_function

        public static Expr integrate_rational_function(Expr p,
                                               Expr q,
                                               Expr x,
                                               boolean arctan)
        Integration of a rational function in Q(x)
        Parameters:
        p - - a polynomial in Q[x]
        q - - a polynomial in Q[x]
        x - - a variable
        arctan - - a boolean
        Returns:
        the function g such that diff(g, x) = p/q.
        if arctan == true, g is a sum of real logs and arctangents with polynomial arguments.
        if arctan == false, g is a sum of real and complex logarithms.

      • hermite_reduction

        public static Expr[] hermite_reduction(Expr p,
                                       Expr q,
                                       Expr x)
        Hermite Reduction in Q(x)
        Parameters:
        p - - a polynomial in Q[x]
        q - - a polynomial in Q[x]
        x - - a variable
        Returns:
        the list [g, h] such that diff(g, x) + h = p/q and h has a square-free denominator.

      • logarithmic_part

        public static Expr[][] logarithmic_part(Expr a,
                                        Expr b,
                                        Expr x)
        The logarithmic part of the integral using Rothstein-Trager method
        Parameters:
        a - - a polynomial in Q[x] with deg(a) < deg(b) and gcd(a, b) = 1
        b - - a polynomial in Q[x] such that gcd(b, diff(b, x)) = 1
        x - - a variable
        Returns:
        the list [[c_1, v_1], ..., [c_k, v_k]] such that
        a/b = sum(c_i*diff(v_i, x)/v_i, i, 1, k)

      • logarithmic_part_lazard_rioboo

        public static Expr[][] logarithmic_part_lazard_rioboo(Expr a,
                                                      Expr b,
                                                      Expr x)
        The logarithmic part of the integral using Lazard-Rioboo improvement
        Parameters:
        a - - a polynomial in Q[x] with deg(a) < deg(b) and gcd(a, b) = 1
        b - - a polynomial in Q[x] such that gcd(b, diff(b, x)) = 1
        x - - a variable
        Returns:

      • log_to_arctan

        public static Expr log_to_arctan(Expr A,
                                 Expr B,
                                 Expr x)
        Converts complex logarithms to real arctangents with polynomial arguments
        Parameters:
        A - - a polynomial in Q[x]
        B - - a polynomial in Q[x] such that B != 0
        x - - a variable
        Returns:
        the function g such that diff(g, x) = diff(i*log((A+I*B)/(A-I*B)), x)
